*gtksourceview-sharp-0.10 (18 May 2005)

  18 May 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  +gtksourceview-sharp-0.10.ebuild:
  Bump.

*gtksourceview-sharp-0.7 (02 Apr 2005)

  02 Apr 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  +gtksourceview-sharp-0.7.ebuild:
  New version that builds against the gtk-sharp-2.0 stuff. Sadly, not easily
  parallel installable with the version that links to gtk-sharp-1.0 items.

*gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r2 (22 Mar 2005)

  22 Mar 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  +gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r2.ebuild:
  Revision bump to not install {vbnet,nemerle}.lang files, which are now
  installed by gtksourceview. See bug #86269

  21 Mar 2005; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org>
  gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc.

  14 Mar 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r1.ebuild, -gtksourceview-sharp-0.5.ebuild:
  Mark stable on x86, make sure we dep on 1.0.x gtk-sharp, and remove on older
  version that didn't include split-up deps.

  10 Mar 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r1.ebuild, gtksourceview-sharp-0.5.ebuild:
  mono moved from dev-dotnet -> dev-lang

  07 Feb 2005; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  gtksourceview-sharp-0.5-r1.ebuild, gtksourceview-sharp-0.5.ebuild:
  Change to using get_libdir, in preperation for a fully supported amd64 mono
  version.

